#//<ip or hostname>/<shared directory> <mount point> cifs guest,uid=1000,iocharset=utf8 0 0

# Mount nfs share
# Note: the value of timeo is in deciseconds i.e. timeo=30 means 3 seconds.
# retrans means the retry. An I/O error is trigger after (retrans * timeo).
# timeo and retrans can be used in soft NFS only.
#<ip or hostname>:/<shared directory> <mount point> nfs noauto,users,rw,atime,soft,timeo=60,retrans=2,nosuid,noexec,nodev,bg,comment=x-gvfs-show 0 0

